# {{PROJECT_NAME}} — Project Memory

## Polling = Dev Lifecycle (MANDATORY)

When user says "start polling" / "poll" / "begin polling":
1. Read `active-role.json` → determine role
2. Read `ai_team_config/procedures/polling-workflow.md` → route to correct lifecycle
3. Execute the FULL lifecycle loop (dev-lifecycle.md or qa-lifecycle.md)

**Two nested loops (dev roles):**
- OUTER: Poll → Assess → Plan → Contracts → [inner loop per issue]
- INNER: Implement → Verify → Document → QA → Iterate

**Single loop (QA roles):**
- Poll → Validate → Verify → Review → Verdict → Complete/Iterate

**NOT passive file watching. NOT running QA checks as dev. NOT just reporting files.**

## Role & Team

- Active role defined in `active-role.json`
- Role details in `ai_team_config/roles/{role_id}.yaml`
- Lifecycle checklists in `ai_team_config/teams/checklists/`
- Procedures in `ai_team_config/procedures/`

## Key Procedures

- Dev lifecycle: `ai_team_config/procedures/dev-lifecycle.md`
- QA lifecycle: `ai_team_config/procedures/qa-lifecycle.md`
- Polling workflow: `ai_team_config/procedures/polling-workflow.md`
- Comms protocol: `ai_team_config/procedures/comms-protocol.md`

## Ownership Rules

- **Dev creates issues**, moves queue/ → active/
- **QA moves active/ → completed/** — Dev NEVER does this
- **Backend-Dev defines contracts** in `contracts/types/`
- **Frontend-Dev consumes contracts** — never writes normalizers

